   [rightbutton.gif] Current Research Areas

          T-13 develops new methods for solving complex problems and
          applies them to problems at the vanguard of technology.
          Computational modeling, quantum computers, and nanotechnology
          are of great interest to researchers in this group. Current
          projects include models of gene regulation, analysis of protein
          and DNA sequences using neural nets and information theory,
          modeling of enhanced oil recovery processes, front-tracking
          techniques, laser-plasma interactions, fundamental turbulence
          modeling, signal enhancement in chaotic processes and
          laser-matter interactions for the Inertial Confinement Fusion
          program.
